                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13218143" author="brandon.williams" created="Tue, 28 Feb 2012 13:12:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;At least one problem here is that CFS.removeDeleted is removing everything here (though listing the hints family in the cli works correctly):&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;ColumnFamily hintsPage = ColumnFamilyStore.removeDeleted(hintStore.getColumnFamily(filter), &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Integer&lt;/span&gt;.MAX_VALUE);
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;At DEBUG you can see the columns collected, but then hintsPage is null.  If we simply change this to:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;ColumnFamily hintsPage = hintStore.getColumnFamily(filter);
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Then at least some of the hints get sent.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13218227" author="jbellis" created="Tue, 28 Feb 2012 14:35:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;removeDeleted should just drop tombstones.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13218248" author="brandon.williams" created="Tue, 28 Feb 2012 14:58:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It&apos;s not too surprising then that a very long and arduous bisect points toward &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-3716&quot; title=&quot;Clean up isMarkedForDelete / getLocalDeletionTime&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-3716&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-3716&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13218289" author="slebresne" created="Tue, 28 Feb 2012 15:45:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-3716&quot; title=&quot;Clean up isMarkedForDelete / getLocalDeletionTime&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-3716&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-3716&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; made it so that purge don&apos;t use the current time internally and is only based on the column local deletion time and the value of gcBefore. So indeed, ColumnFamilyStore.removeDeleted(c, Integer.MAX_VALUE) will remove every expiring column since it basically means &apos;remove everything that will be expired at the end of time&apos;. The current time should be used instead as gcBefore. Not sure what is the remaining problem though if it doesn&apos;t fix it fully.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13218325" author="brandon.williams" created="Tue, 28 Feb 2012 16:29:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;That does indeed fix it.  Patch to use the current time when filtering tombstones.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13218328" author="jbellis" created="Tue, 28 Feb 2012 16:31:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13218334" author="brandon.williams" created="Tue, 28 Feb 2012 16:35:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
